#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.144"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.144:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.144:0.2"
msgid "15. Tikaṇḍakīvagga"
msgstr "15. At Tikaṇḍakī"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.144:0.3"
msgid "144. Tikaṇḍakīsutta"
msgstr "144. At Tikaṇḍakī"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.144:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sākete viharati tikaṇḍakīvane."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāketa, in Tikaṇḍakī Wood."

msgctxt "an5.144:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an5.144:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an5.144:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an5.144:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.144:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant would do well to meditate from time to time "
"perceiving the following:"

#. </p><ol><li>
#. VAR: appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī → appaṭikkūle paṭikkūlasaññī (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.144:2.2"
msgid "appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya."
msgstr "the repulsive in the unrepulsive,"

#. </li><li>
msgctxt "an5.144:2.3"
msgid ""
"Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyya."
msgstr "the unrepulsive in the repulsive,"

#. </li><li>
msgctxt "an5.144:2.4"
msgid ""
"Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca "
"paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya."
msgstr "the repulsive in both the unrepulsive and the repulsive, and"

#. </li><li>
msgctxt "an5.144:2.5"
msgid ""
"Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca "
"appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyya."
msgstr "the unrepulsive in both the repulsive and the unrepulsive."

#. </li><li>
msgctxt "an5.144:2.6"
msgid ""
"Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ "
"abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyya sato sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant would do well to meditate from time to time staying equanimous, "
"mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive."

#. </li></ol><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: Kiñca → kathañca (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an5.144:3.1"
msgid ""
"Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī "
"vihareyya?"
msgstr ""
"For what reason should a mendicant meditate perceiving the repulsive in the "
"unrepulsive?"

msgctxt "an5.144:3.2"
msgid "‘Mā me rajanīyesu dhammesu rāgo udapādī’ti—"
msgstr "‘May greed not arise in me for things that arouse greed.’"

msgctxt "an5.144:3.3"
msgid ""
"idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī "
"vihareyya."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant should meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive for "
"this reason."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.144:4.1"
msgid ""
"Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī "
"vihareyya?"
msgstr ""
"For what reason should a mendicant meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in "
"the repulsive?"

msgctxt "an5.144:4.2"
msgid "‘Mā me dosanīyesu dhammesu doso udapādī’ti—"
msgstr "‘May hate not arise in me for things that provoke hate.’ …"

msgctxt "an5.144:4.3"
msgid ""
"idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī "
"vihareyya."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.170"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.144:5.1"
msgid ""
"Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca "
"paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya?"
msgstr ""
"For what reason should a mendicant meditate perceiving the repulsive in both "
"the unrepulsive and the repulsive?"

msgctxt "an5.144:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘Mā me rajanīyesu dhammesu rāgo udapādi, mā me dosanīyesu dhammesu doso "
"udapādī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘May greed not arise in me for things that arouse greed. May hate not arise "
"in me for things that provoke hate.’ …"

msgctxt "an5.144:5.3"
msgid ""
"idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca "
"paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.144:6.1"
msgid ""
"Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca "
"appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyya?"
msgstr ""
"For what reason should a mendicant meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in "
"both the repulsive and the unrepulsive?"

msgctxt "an5.144:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘Mā me dosanīyesu dhammesu doso udapādi, mā me rajanīyesu dhammesu rāgo "
"udapādī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘May hate not arise in me for things that provoke hate. May greed not arise "
"in me for things that arouse greed.’ …"

msgctxt "an5.144:6.3"
msgid ""
"idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca "
"appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyya."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.144:7.1"
msgid ""
"Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca "
"tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyya?"
msgstr ""
"For what reason should a mendicant meditate staying equanimous, mindful and "
"aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive?"

# BB’s “anywhere” for katthaci relies on the over-literal comm. gloss kisminci padese. It’s better to see this as locative of reference, “in any respect”, hence being a duplication.
#. VAR: kvacani → kvacini (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: kiñcanaṃ → kiñcana (bj, pts1) | kiñcina (s1-3)
msgctxt "an5.144:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘Sato sampajāno mā me kvacani katthaci kiñcanaṃ rajanīyesu dhammesu rāgo "
"udapādi, mā me kvacani katthaci kiñcanaṃ dosanīyesu dhammesu doso udapādi, "
"mā me kvacani katthaci kiñcanaṃ mohanīyesu dhammesu moho udapādī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘May no greed for things that arouse greed, hate for things that provoke "
"hate, or delusion for things that promote delusion arise in me in any way at "
"all.’"

msgctxt "an5.144:7.3"
msgid ""
"idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca "
"tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyya sato sampajāno”ti."
msgstr ""
"For this reason a mendicant should meditate staying equanimous, mindful and "
"aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.144:7.4"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
